Learn the pros and cons of owning a rottweiler from dog expert Julia Szabo in this Howcast video.


I'm Julia Szabo, also known as a Pet Reporter, and I am the "Living with Dogs" columnist for dogster.com. I've actually written 6 books and I'm hard at work on my next one. It will be about about dogs -- that's as much as I can say right now. I love dogs and I think nobody's life is complete without one. So I'm here to tell you about a variety of different dogs breeds that might suit your lifestyle. I hope you'll adopt one soon. The Rottweiler is an amazing dog. And actually, if you want to be really technical, because it is a German breed, the W is pronounced as a V, like victory. So it's Rott-Veiler. There is actually a statue in Rotweill, Germany of a Rottweiler, a beautiful dog. These dogs were originally used as working dogs, and they still are used as working dogs. But this is a great example of a dog whose job has evolved to meet, you know, and match what humans need. In the old days, the Rottweiler was actually used as a drover. They actually drove cattle and other livestocks for the people who were butchering them. They also accompanied butchers to market. And the money was often tied around their neck, because, who's gonna mess with a Rottweiler? But, in reality, they're actually very cuddly, wonderful dogs. The Rottweiler now works in search and rescue...they do therapy work. They are service dogs also, because they're very strong. They pull things. You know, they're just amazing all around, strong working dogs, and they like to have a job. Similar to a pitbull, a Rottweiler really does need a strong hand, a strong but gentle hand in training. That's very important for a dog like a Rottweiler, so that he or she doesn't become aggressive. So I've gotten to know many of them, I love this breed. They make wonderful dogs, and I think they're beautiful. Just the black glossy coat with the brown marking. They often have little eyebrows. And sometimes when you see mutts with eyebrows, it's pretty easy to figure out that there's some Rottweiler in the lineage.
title: Pros & Cons of a Rottweiler | Dog Breeds

description:
The Grey Partridge (Perdix perdix) also known as the English Partridge, Hungarian Partridge, or Hun, is a gamebird in the pheasant family Phasianidae of the order Galliformes, gallinaceous birds. The species has been successfully introduced to many parts of the world for shooting, including vast areas of North America, where it is most commonly known as Hungarian partridge, or just "Hun". Widespread and common throughout its large range, the Grey Partridge is evaluated as Least Concern on the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. This partridge breeds on farmland across most of Europe into western Asia, and has been introduced widely into North America. They are quite common in some areas of southern Canada and the northern United States.

The Grey Partridge is a rotund bird, 28--32 cm long, brown-backed, with grey flanks and chest. The belly is white, usually marked with a large chestnut-brown horse-shoe mark in males, and also in many females. Hens lay up to twenty eggs in a ground nest. The nest is usually in the margin of a cereal field, most commonly Winter wheat. The only major and constant difference between the sexes is the so-called cross of Lorraine on the tertiary coverts of females -- these being marked with two transverse bars, as opposed to the one in males. These are present after around 16 weeks of age when the birds have moulted into adult plumage. Young Grey Partridges are mostly yellow-brown and lack the distinctive face and underpart markings. The song is a harsh kieerr-ik, and when disturbed, like most of the gamebirds, it flies a short distance on rounded wings, often calling rick rick rick as it rises. They are a seed-eating species, but the young in particular take insects as an essential protein supply. During the first 10 days of life, the young can only digest insects. The parents lead their chicks to the edges of cereal fields, where they can forage for insects. They are also a non-migratory terrestrial species, and form flocks outside the breeding season.

Source : Wikipedia

description:
Watch more How to Do Muay Thai Kickboxing videos: http://www.howcast.com/videos/504051-5-Facts-about-Kickboxing-Muay-Thai

Learn how to do five tactics to counter kicking attacks in kickboxing from Mushin MMA's Sean Hinds in this muay Thai training video from Howcast.


Countering Against Kicking Attacks. There are two different ways to counter the kicking attacks. Alright? The first one and most common on is once I've blocked a roundhouse kick with my leg, I come down and then I return back with a kick of my own. Okay? So I'm going to defend my opponent's left roundhouse kick. Okay? I block and then from the block I come down and then come straight up with my own roundhouse. One more time. I block, come down, up, and then up with my own roundhouse kick. 

Now, when I block with the left one, also come with a block. I'm not going to put the leg down in front and then switch because now it takes a little bit too much time to go through the motions. So after I block from this position here now, I'm going to shoot forward with the right foot and then go right into the kick from there. Okay? So, I'm going to block the right roundhouse kick. I block, and then up from there. Again. Block, and then up from there. Okay? 

Now, the other one. If my opponent decides to throw his left roundhouse kick, if I don't have the time to block with the right leg, I can come up and I can use a front push kick or a teep (?) in order to put him off of balance now. So he comes up with that left roundhouse kick, I drop the left teep (?), puts him off of balance, now I can close the distance and now go into attack now. Again. 

When you come up with that push kick, make sure you pick your knee up nice and high so when you go out, your foot ends up pretty much in the middle of the chest so you can get good movement out of your opponent. Okay? So again, he comes up with that left roundhouse. I go up and then now I can come in. When he attacks with his right roundhouse, I'm going to come up with my right leg (okay?) in the same motion again. Up. Again, up. And then extend the leg out and again now I can attack in with punches or kicks. Alright.

Now we have my opponent throws a kick up high. I may not be able to block the kick with my leg, so I'm going to take the impact. Once I've taken the impact, I come right back down and I throw my kick towards the thigh. So when you speed it up and you go up, bop, bap. Again. He comes up, bop, bap. Alright? And that is defending some of the attacking kicks.
title: 5 Tactics to Counter Kicking Attacks | Muay Thai

description:
Southern Cross (referred to as Crux: Latin for cross), is the smallest of the 88 modern constellations. Crux is one of the most distinctive in the Southern Hemisphere. It holds considerable cultural significance in Australia, Brazil, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea and Samoa, so much so that the five stars which comprise the constellation are emblazoned on the respective flags of each country.

This selection, unlike the other pieces in my "Outback Suite", is quite dissonant. There are numerous major and minor second-chords, tone clusters and similar discords of polytonality which reflect the music of Charles Ives. One may note very subtle variations on Waltzing Matilda in the bass-clef from time to time. 

Music © 2014 John Steven Lasher. All Rights Reserved.
title: Southern Cross from "Outback Suite" for piano. Composed by John Steven Lasher.

Luke Rudkowski attempts to question Obama's Senior Campaign Adviser, Robert Gibbs on the Obama administration's appeal to keep the indefinite detention provision of the NDAA. With no response about the NDAA, Luke later asks Robert Gibbs on how President Obama will defend having a secret kill list in the debates. Gibbs gives a standard response on the administration doing what it has to do to handle the threat of Alqaeda. Sierra Adamson then follows up by questioning if there is justification for killings such as Anwar al-Awlaki's 16 year old son who was an American citizen, to which Gibbs lays the blame of his death on Anwar al-Awlaki not being a responsible father.

New York Time's article on President Obama's kill list: http://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/29/world/obamas-leadership-in-war-on-al-qaeda.html

Abdulrahman al-Awlaki, the son of Anwar al-Awlaki, was a 16 year old American citizen born in Denver. He was killed in October 2011 in Yemen by drone strikes that were separate to those that killed his father.

The three-dimensional (3D) drawing allows the effect. In the three-dimensional (3D) space,  the lines are half as long in the depth. The human eye follows the lines and the human brain concludes the different sizes. It is only a Illusion, the effect is lost after a long observation period. 
Incredible and Awesome SCIENCE EXPERIMENT Full HD - 1080p - Leroy Fuellgraf
Channel: http://www.youtube.com/TheCoolPhysics

Optische Illusionen! Du denkst du siehst geometrische Objekte mit unterschiedlichen Seitengrößen, aber es ist nur eine optische Illusion. Alle Seiten haben die selbe Form und Größe. Das dreidimensionale (3D) zeichnen erlaubt den Effekt. Im dreidimensionalen Raum sind in der Tiefe die Linien stets halb so lang. Das menschliche Auge folgt den Linien und das menschliche Gehirn interpretiert die unterschiedlichen Größen. Es ist nur eine Illusion, der Effekt verliert mit der Betrachtungszeit.

Illusion d'optique! Vous pensez, vous voyez des objets géométriques avec différentes parties de tailles, mais c'est une illusion d'optique impressionnante. description:
Amb el lema "La festa és donar sang", l'ajuntament, l'Associació de Donants de Sang de Girona, el Departament de Salut de la Generalitat de Catalunya i el Banc de Sang i Teixits, organitzen la 2a Marató de Donació de Sang de Castell--Platja d'Aro el proper dissabte 24 de setembre. L'activitat es concentrarà a la sala d'actes de la planta baixa de l'Ajuntament de 10 a 14 h i de 16 a 21 h. Durant tota la jornada hi haurà activitats diverses i actuacions a la Plaça Major de Platja d'Aro (molt propera a l'Ajuntament), amb un espai lúdic amb animació musical, inflables per a la mainada, un taller de globoflèxia, servei de guarderia gratuït, un refrigeri especial i obsequi per a tots els donants i un marcador electrònic que anirà indicant l'evolució de la marató, amb la voluntat i l'objectiu d'assolir un mínim de 200 donants.

Al Banc de Sang i Teixits li calen més de 1.000 donacions de sang al dia per tal de garantir que tots tinguem sang quan ho necessitem per a intervencions quirúrgiques, per a tractaments oncològics, per a trasplantaments, i en cas d'accidents greus. Es pot donar sang si es té entre 18 i 70 anys i si es pesa un mínim de 50 quilos, els homes poden donar sang quatre vegades a l'any i les dones tres. Per donar sang no cal estar en dejú; si es té algun dubte es pot consultar als professionals; i sempre s'utilitza material d'un sol ús.
title: Marató de donació de sang · Platja d'Aro 2011

Blog: onedelicateheart.blogspot.com
 INSTAGRAM: 1delicateheart
 
Hi guys, this slideshow is a continuation of my last one I made in 2013 http://youtu.be/DCXp4oUeYGU. I am still in recovery from Cushing's disease from a adrenal gland tumor. I have Adrenal insufficiency since my adrenalactomy and still on hormone replacement. I still continued to improve after the last video I made and want to share with you guys the progress. As you can see my whole face changed eversince the adrenalectomy and thank goodness the acne and moon face went away. I am starting to look more feminine now that the steroids are not as much in my body. I have lost a bit too much weight from lack of appetite but I am not complaining! Sorry for the vain pics I am just so happy to have my face back even though. I believe keeping progress pics help remind us cushie's that we are improving!! I look super tired I know I will look healthier when I fully recover. The psychiatric problems improved and I am off antidepressants! I want you to know that it takes years to bounce back so be patient and stay strong!
email me: yumnguyen07@yahoo.com
title: My Cushing's Recovery Part 2 (NEW 2014)
